| v13 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v13.scad | Superseded — bore axis defaulted to Z (rotate_extrude's native axis) instead of the required X, bell sat vertically like a chimney cap instead of forming a T-junction with the crossbar. Fixed in v14. |
| v14 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v14.scad | Superseded — fixed bore orientation correctly (confirmed by Janis's real render screenshots) but left two real proportion problems visible in those renders: ~24mm vertical gap between neck and bell (positioned independently), and neck OD (built around old 50mm pole_od) visually overpowering the bell's narrow waist. Fixed in v15. |
| v15 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v15.scad | **ACTIVE** — two fixes per Janis's v14 render review. ISSUE 1 (gap): pole_top_bell()'s local origin (small face, local Z=0) translates to world (cx,cy,xbar_z) before rotate/scale reorient around that fixed point, so the bell's small face sits at world Z=xbar_z exactly; neck_top = xbar_z + neck_bell_overlap (0.2mm) replaces the old independent z0 formula, seating the neck 0.2mm into the bell's small face for a clean manifold union (both siblings in same color() block, Rule M-1). pole_body() height extended to reach the new neck bottom with no visible gap there either (visual-contact only, components remain logically separate). ISSUE 2 (diameter): pole_od 50mm→40mm (Janis-approved, still above 36mm market floor), neck_wall_t 6mm→3mm/side, neck_id kept at unchanged v13/v14 formula (pole_d+1=41mm) so neck_od = 47mm — ⚑ FLAG: 1mm more than Janis's stated 46mm formula (pole_od+2×3mm) due to preserving the unchanged slip-fit clearance mechanism; both values documented for Janis to confirm. ⚑ FLAG: bell's actual waist (computed via Python Bezier sampling, NOT at the small end-face but partway along the concave curve) is ≈44.5mm diameter at z≈16.8mm — the new 47mm neck_od (and even Janis's stated 46mm) still EXCEEDS this waist by ~1.5-2.5mm, proportion much improved vs v14's 63mm neck_od but not a clean fit yet; not resolved since bell exterior profile is explicitly DO NOT TOUCH this round. ⚑ FLAG: pole_base_collar()'s collar_id = pole_d+1 cascades automatically with the pole_d change (51mm→41mm) — its own code untouched, automatic side effect of the approved dimension change. Bore diameter (33mm), bore axis (X, re-verified unchanged), bell exterior profile, M6 through-bolt mechanism, pole_base_collar(), crossbar — unchanged from v14. ⚑ FLAG (carried over): pole_body() still has no through-holes for the M6 bolts to align against. rules-dimensions.md updated (v6→v7) to reflect pole_od=40mm. |

